  <li>Products donâ€™t link to a comparison chart. It can be difficult to figure out why one product is more $$ than another without multiple page switches. (The product pages themselves DO have this, but only when you click â€˜Buy Nowâ€™)</li>
  <li>Clicking â€˜Buyâ€™ on a product page doesnâ€™t actually add the product to your cart, it takes you to the store where you have to â€˜add to cartâ€™ again.</li>
  <li>The â€˜Buy Nowâ€™ button on the page doesnâ€™t buy it now. In fact it just pops up a menu where youâ€™re <em>at least</em> 8 more clicks from buying it (4 of which are trying to get to checkout!)</li>
  <li>Itâ€™s slow. The store is so very slow. It may be because thereâ€™s a sale going on right now, but thatâ€™s not a particularly good reason.</li>
  <li>â€˜Apply Discount Codeâ€™ doesnâ€™t apply a discount code. It pops up another section for you to enter a discount code <em>then you click again</em> to enter the code. Strange.</li>
  <li>â€˜Sort By Positionâ€™ is the default sort. Interesting.</li>
